{"questionId":"21561","questionHtml":"<p>A black-body radiator emits a peak wavelength of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>max</mtext></msub></math> and a maximum power of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>. The peak&nbsp;wavelength emitted by a second black-body radiator with the same surface area is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>max</mtext></msub></math>.&nbsp;What is the total power of the second black-body radiator?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"21561","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.29","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A black-body radiator emits a peak wavelength of λmax and a maximum power of P0. The peak wavelength emitted by a second black-body radiator with the same surface area is 2 λmax. W","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"29","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Energy production","8.2 – Thermal energy transfer","Core","Topic 8: Energy production"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}